General Assembly Raised Bill No. 131
February Session, 2026 LCO No. 811
Referred to Committee on COMMERCE
Introduced by:
(CE)
AN ACT CONCERNING MANUFACTURING.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General
Assembly convened:
1 Section 1. (Effective from passage) The Commissioner of Economic and
2 Community Development shall conduct a study relating to the needs of
3 manufacturers in the state. Not later than January 1, 2027, the
4 Department of Economic and Community Development shall submit a
5 report of the results of such study to the joint standing committee of the
6 General Assembly having cognizance of matters relating to commerce,
7 in accordance with the provisions of section 11-4a of the general statutes.
This act shall take effect as follows and shall amend the following
sections:
Section 1 from passage New section
CE Joint Favorable
LCO 811 1 of 1

